summary: Combined w/ the complete lack of either denials or some kind of "leave my personal life alone", he and Phil created the ideal...
question: Combined w/ the complete lack of either denials or some kind of "leave my personal life alone", he and Phil created the ideal atmosphere for phannies, and they know that. One denial in 2019 would literally shock them, they're so not used to it, their whole belief system would crumble and they'd only have fanfiction to soothe themselves with
answer:
And if he or Phil said that they’re in relationship(s) with someone else or are both single, only mentally unstable, paranoid tin hatters would make a theory out of it. But most of those are too busy with kpop and the larry stylinson fandom already. So Dan often over-compensates w/ his phan service, which doesn’t do his and Phil’s reputation any favours because it feeds an over-dramatic, entitled fandom.

question: 'He could literally release a sex tape of him and anyone other than Phil, get legally married to that person, and never speak to Phil again and people would still find a way to make it “phan proof.” ' do you honestly think so? lol If he denied being in a romantic relationship w/ Phil once now, most people would drop it and move on to kpop or to the bohemian rhapsody fandom in which shipping has got popular recently, or whatever.
answer:
Many, maybe even most, probably would, but I believe you are sorely underestimating how much some people will cling to things. Aren’t there some people who believe the Harry Styles’ baby was a prop and Benedict Cumberbatch’s family are fake? I know people still believe that kind of stuff about the actors on Supernatural because I’ve seen that old psycho William Shatner rant about it on Twitter.

I have seen ship sinkings in fandoms though too and I actually always maintain that one of the reasons people cling so hard to ships even if they don’t seem to be really into the ship itself anymore is because it holds the community together and that’s what people are most scared of losing as the ship goes down. I guess I’m hoping they make a comeback with the content so shipping isn’t the be all and end all either way.

summary: I honestly think Dan has made himself a promise to not be on any social media for the whole month of January, and only post when...
body:
I honestly think Dan has made himself a promise to not be on any social media for the whole month of January, and only post when he had to, ( like the ii watch party, phil’s birthday, a few tweets here and there to just let us know he hasn’t completely disappeared.)

And if he has indeed been out running almost every day of January, that shows he’s put himself and his health first, and that he’s wanted to do some serious self-care after all the craziness of 2018. 

I think that’s what he’s been up to. Taking a step back from being the “Entertainer Dan” and just be “Dan”, without having to entertain, without having our eyes on him. Just him doing something for himself without pressure.  

And it wouldn’t surprise me if his first video of 2019 is about this, about self-care and taking a step back from everything for a while. 

This is just my thoughts on this whole thing though, we’ll see what happens.
